At Mercedes-Benz Malaysia Sdn Bhd and/or Mercedes-Benz Services Malaysia Sdn Bhd (“Mercedes-Benz”, “we”, “us” or “our”), we are committed to the protection of your Personal Data in and outside of Malaysia. This privacy notice (“Notice”) explains the collection of, processing of, disclosure of and your rights over your Personal Data pursuant to the Personal Data Protection Act 2010 of Malaysia (“Act”).

This Notice applies to all Personal Data which you have and/or will be provided to us and supplements any other privacy notices which may apply. This Notice does not apply to our products and services which have separate privacy notices that do not incorporate this Notice and to those products, services and/or activities offered by other providers wherein Mercedes-Benz has no influence over nor be responsible for the processing of such Personal Data by the third party provider (e.g. websites which you may access via links on our websites or services handled by third party providers which offered in our mobile applications, specific Social Media Platforms, App Stores and Advertising Networks which you have consented for your Personal Data to be transferred to). Please refer to the relevant third-party providers’ terms of use and privacy notice for such processing of your Personal Data which can be obtained from the relevant third party providers’ websites, mobile applications and/or online portals.

“Personal Data” means information about you, from which you can be directly or indirectly identified, which you have provided to Mercedes-Benz including but not limited to when you request for information, sign up for our products and/or services, enter into any commercial transactions with Mercedes-Benz and/or its related companies, upon registration as a user on any of our websites, online portals or mobile applications or through cookies on our websites, and may include but not limited to your name, age, identity card number, passport number, address, gender, date of birth, online identity, instant messenger IDs, social network addresses, Mercedes me ID, children basic details, marital status, occupation, bank account details, credit card details, income range, contact information, email address, employer, race, ethnic origin, nationality, body height, location data, media preference and usage, viewing, technical and device data (e.g. your browser or device type, cookies, unique device identifier, IP address), data about your vehicles (e.g., vehicle identification numbers, license plate, vehicle configurations, mileage, for Mercedes-Benz vehicles also data in the digital service book, duration of linkage to the Mercedes Me ID, diagnosis data and codes), data about products that you have expressed interested in, used or purchased (e.g., details of purchase and lease agreements, order dates, delivery dates, vehicle configurations stored, information on the processing of guarantee and goodwill cases, payment methods, distribution channel and retailer information, respective contract status) and data about services that you have expressed interested in, or used or purchased (e.g., details of purchase and lease agreements, order dates, delivery dates and termination dates, Mercedes me connect services booked, error codes, repair data, mileage, information on the processing of guarantee and goodwill cases, repair location, costs and payment methods, distribution channel and retailer information, respective contract status) and any additional information relating to you. In the event that you provide us with any Personal Data relating to a third party identifiable from your Personal Data (e.g. information of your spouse, children, parents and/or employees), you represent to us that you have obtained the consent of the third party for us to process their Personal Data in accordance with this Notice.

Please also refer to our ‘Settings’ section of the websites, mobile applications, online portals or MBUX Multimedia System which shall also form part of this Notice for the purposes of your consent.

Obligatory Personal Data and Impact Resulting from Failure to Supply Personal Data

It is obligatory to provide us with your Personal Data where it is indicated as such in any of our application, registration, contact, request, order, reservation or payment forms which may be provided to you physically, through our online portals, websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System (“Obligatory Personal Data”). Obligatory Personal Data are those that we require in order to provide you with our products and/or services. The failure to supply such Obligatory Personal Data may affect your ability to use our products, services, online features, MBUX Multimedia System and/or access to member-restricted portal as well as being unable to provide you with the products and services that you have registered and subscribed for, updates on our latest products, services, promotions, events and/or launches, proceed with your reservation and/or process your payment transaction (“Products and Services”). Voluntary personal data are those that are not mandatory in order for us to provide you with our Products and Services (“Voluntary Personal Data”). If you do not provide us with Voluntary Personal Data, you can still sign up for our Products and Services.

How We Collect and Process Your Data

We will collect your Personal Data in the following manner and sources:

a) When you commence a business relationship with us or when you enter into any commercial transactions or execution of a contract with us;

b) When you register a user account on any of our websites, online portals or mobile applications;

c) When you access, browse on or use our websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System, including but not limited to cookies used on our websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System, browsers and operating systems you use, the date and time of your visit, the access status (e.g. whether you were able to open a website and/or mobile application or received an error message), the use of website, mobile application and/or the MBUX Multimedia System functions, the use of advertisements of Mercedes-Benz (including advertisements on third party websites and/or mobile applications), any search terms you may have entered, the frequency with which you open individual websites and/or mobile applications, the names of files you retrieve, the transferred data quantity, the website and/or mobile application from which you accessed our websites and/or mobile applications and the website and/or mobile application you visit after having visited our websites and/or mobile applications either by clicking links on our websites and/or mobile applications or by directly entering a domain in the input field of the same tab (or the same window) of the browser you used to open our websites and/or mobile applications. For security reasons, in particular to prevent and detect attacks on our website, mobile applications and/or the MBUX Multimedia System or fraudulent behaviour, we also save your IP address and the name of your internet service provider for a period of seven (7) days;

d) When you use and access any features in the MBUX Multimedia System;

e) When you use the emails on products and services sent to you (e.g. how often you open such emails, which links you click in the emails);

f) When you contact us through various methods such as application forms, order forms, contact forms, emails and letters, a chat, social media platforms including but not limited to Facebook, Twitter and Instagram, telephone calls and/or conversations you have with our staff and/or our Mercedes-Benz Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers. If you contact us or we contact you using any telecommunications platform, we may monitor or record the telephone call for quality assurance, training and security purposes;

g) When you browse or use our online store to purchase and/or reserve vehicles, whether by login, register or guest checkout;

h) When you use or obtain any of our Products and Services;

i) When you participate in any surveys, questionnaires, competitions, contests, offers, promotions or otherwise interact with us online or offline via an appointed third party;

j) From such other third-party sources where you have given your consent for the disclosure of Personal Data relating to you, and/or where otherwise lawfully permitted; and/or

k) From publicly available sources.

In the event that the circumstances listed in paragraphs (a) to (k) above result in sharing of personal information relating to other persons (for example your family members, employees or friends) with us, you confirm that, you have obtained their consent or otherwise entitled to provide their personal information to us and for us to use according to this Notice, and you have informed them to read this Notice.

Processing of Personal Data for Purchase of Mercedes-Benz Products, Features and Services or Payment to Mercedes-Benz

We will process your data for the purpose of and to the extent required to fulfil a purchase contract, reservation order or payment instruction. In this context we may pass on customer data to a Mercedes-Benz Group AG company, Mercedes-Benz Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers (“Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers”) and/or contractual partner to the extent necessary in order to process and fulfil the purchase contract, reservation order or payment instruction.

Furthermore, we may process your Personal Data which we receive in connection with the provision of the purchase contract, reservation order or payment instruction for the protection of our legitimate interests (assertion, exercise or defence of legal claims), for the protection of the data and/or information processing systems required for performance of the contract or for the fulfilment of the legal obligations, and may provide such data to third parties (in particular government authorities) to the extent required for investigating any violations against the general terms and conditions, misuse of services or attempts to gain unauthorised access to information processing systems or to data of other customers.

The Personal Data will be stored for the duration of the contractual relationship and will subsequently be retained for such period as may be necessary to protect our interests and/or where otherwise required by law including but not limited to legal commercial and legal tax record-keeping requirements.

We have appointed technical service providers and payment service providers to handle and manage payment transactions. These companies may be located outside of Malaysia and have access only to such Personal Data as are required to perform their tasks. These service providers have concluded service contracts with us or any Mercedes-Benz Group AG company, as the case may be, which contain provisions on the handling and protection of personal data.

In order to conclude the purchase transaction, reservation order or payment instruction, it may be necessary to transfer the corresponding payment transaction data (e.g. bank account number or credit card number, name of card holder, card’s period of validity, amount and time of payment) to the technical service providers and payment service providers for the electronic payment transaction made. To proceed and complete the payment transaction, you hereby consent to such processing and/or transfer of Personal Data.

You may keep your payment data (e.g. credit card details) available for future payments made via our websites, mobile applications or in-car MBUX Multimedia System linked to the Mercedes me Portal, and such stored payment data will be processed at your request by Mercedes pay GmbH.

This service can be deactivated or stored data can be managed at any time under “My data” on our Mercedes me Portal.

Further information on data processing by Mercedes pay GmbH can be found at the following link:

Data privacy statement of Mercedes pay GmbH

Processing of Personal Data for Purchase of Mercedes-Benz Products, Features and Services or Payment to Mercedes-Benz in the MBUX Multimedia System

This data protection information applies when you purchase Mercedes-Benz products, features and/or services or made payment via the MBUX Multimedia System. It applies exclusively to this “Store in the Vehicle”.

1. Collection and processing of personal data when you visit the “Store in the Vehicle”

When you visit the “Store in the Vehicle”, Personal Data such as your user ID and vehicle identification number will be processed and stored for the purpose of presenting the available range of products, features and services. To enable presentation of the range of products, features and services and to facilitate the ordering process, within the Mercedes me connect environment, Mercedes-Benz Group AG may forward customer data to us.

Your Personal Data will be deleted as soon as the purpose for which we have collected and processed the data no longer applies unless it is necessary to be retained to protect our interests and/or where otherwise required by law.

2. Collection and processing of personal data in connection with an order

We process your Personal Data for the purpose of and to the extent necessary for the order process and fulfilment of the purchase contract, reservation order or payment instruction. For this purpose, your Personal Data may be passed on to the relevant Mercedes-Benz Group AG company, Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers and/or contractual partner for the contractual performance or completing the payment transaction.

We have appointed technical service providers and payment service providers to handle and manage payment transactions. These companies may be located outside of Malaysia and have access only to such Personal Data as are required to perform their tasks. These service providers have concluded service contracts with us or any Mercedes-Benz Group AG company, as the case may be, which contain provisions on the handling and protection of personal data.

Furthermore, we may process your Personal Data which we receive in connection with performance of the contract or completing the payment transaction for the protection of our legitimate interests (assertion, exercise or defence of legal claims), for the protection of the data and/or information processing systems required for performance of the contract or for the fulfilment of the legal obligations, and may provide such data to third parties (in particular government authorities) to the extent required for investigating any violations against the general terms and conditions, misuse of services or attempts to gain unauthorised access to information processing systems or to data of other customers.

The Personal Data will be stored for the duration of the contractual relationship and will subsequently be retained for such period as may be necessary to protect our interests and/or where otherwise required by law including but not limited to legal commercial and legal tax record-keeping requirements.

Processing of Personal Data for Direct Marketing

This data protection information applies when you provide your consent to process your Personal Data for the purposes of direct marketing, whereby you consented to be contacted electronically (e.g. email, SMS, MMS, whatsapp message, push notification, in-car-message), by telephone and by postal mailing for us as well as Mercedes-Benz Group AG company, Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers and/or our contractual partner to use your data to inform you in accordance with your interest about Mercedes-Benz products and services.

We will process your Personal Data for the purpose of direct marketing in accordance with the specific consent you have given to us.

Your consent declaration – as well as any withdrawal of a consent – will be transferred to Mercedes-Benz Group AG company, Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers and/or our contractual partner along with your contact details necessary to match it to you. The companies that are entitled to contact you based on your consent declaration, can consult your consent declaration to make sure that you are only contacted according to your preferences. In addition, each controller may deploy third party processors such as IT service providers or marketing agencies.

To the extent you consent to the transfer of data to specific Social Media Platforms, App Stores and Advertising Networks, some or all of the recipients are located or may have relevant operations outside of Malaysia, such as in the Europe and USA. In such instances, you consent to the transfer of your Personal Data outside of Malaysia.

Your Personal Data will be retained by each controller for no longer than necessary to achieve the purposes described, and for a maximum of five (5) years after the date of the last interaction with us, or for any further duration required by virtue of applicable retention obligations applicable to the relevant data controller.

You may withdraw your consent for direct marketing purposes at any time by notice in writing to us. If you withdraw your consent, you may not be contacted with information and advice about Mercedes-Benz products and services. Your withdrawal of consent for direct marketing purposes will not affect any other individual consent which you have given in the past or will give in the future, which remains valid until such individual consent is revoked by you.

Use of Personal Data, Limitation of Purpose

Personal Data collected by Mercedes-Benz may be used for, but not limited to the extent necessary for the purposes of:

a) technical administration of the website, mobile applications and/or MBUX Multimedia System, for customer management;

b) improving our websites, mobile applications and/or MBUX Multimedia System to be as user-friendly as possible and protecting our IT systems from attacks and other illegal activities;

c) handling any business transactions and settling the appurtenant accounts;

d) for product surveys and/or statistical analysis;

e) for conclusion of a purchase contract or reservation order of vehicles you have selected;

f) for billing and/or processing the payment transaction (includes transaction handles and manages by third party technical service provider and/or payment service provider);

g) providing services to you or in responding to any query from you and/or your representative;

h) for our internal record-keeping;

i) for internal investigations;

j) communicating with you;

k) taxation and/or auditing purposes;

l) conducting events, programmes, client promotional activities, and marketing in connection with our services;

m) sending material such as newsletters, articles and other updates;

n) for the repairs, servicing and maintenance of your vehicle with our Mercedes-Benz Authorized Service Dealers;

o) other purposes (e.g. display of personalised content or advertising based on your user behaviour), and possibly selected third parties use of your data, providing you give your consent;

p) direct marketing (e.g. informing you about Mercedes-Benz products and services that closely align to your interest);

q) for the protection of our legitimate interests (assertion, exercise or defence of legal claims);

r) for the exercise of any functions conferred or obligation imposed on any person by law and/or towards the administration of justice; and/or

s) for any purpose incidental, ancillary or in furtherance to the abovementioned purposes.

(collectively referred to as “Purposes”)

Disclosure

Personal Data provided to us will generally be kept confidential but you hereby consent and authorise us to provide or disclose your Personal Data to the following categories of parties:

a) Any person to whom we are compelled or required to do so under the law or in response to a competent or government agency;

b) Any person to whom you have granted access to the products, services or other means of communication which we have provided or are providing to you;

c) Any Mercedes-Benz Group AG company and/or any of our related companies and subsidiaries including those established in the future, in Malaysia and all other countries;

d) Any third-party offers which available on our websites, mobile applications, online portals or MBUX Multimedia System;

e) Any third-party providers which handle and manage the Products and Services which are to be provided to you;

f) Our appointed payment service providers and/or technical service providers for purposes of handling, managing and processing the payment transactions;

g) Our Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers;

h) Our strategic business partners and authorised representatives;

i) Any Mercedes-Benz Group AG company and/or our contractual partner which you have consented to use your data for direct marketing purposes;

j) Our auditors, consultants, accountants, lawyers or other financial or professional advisers;

k) Our sub-contractors or third party service or product providers as may be determined to be necessary or appropriate.

Safeguards

We shall keep and process your Personal Data in a secure manner. We endeavour, where practicable, to implement the appropriate administrative and security safeguards and procedures in accordance with the applicable laws and regulations to prevent the unauthorised or unlawful processing of your Personal Data and the accidental loss of, destruction of, damage to, or manipulation of your Personal Data. We shall keep you informed of any breach to your Personal Data where we are legally required to do so. While we endeavour to take all reasonable steps to safeguard your Personal Data and keep your Personal Data protected, there may be situations where you are linked to external websites or mobile applications while using our websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System, which we shall not be held responsible for the data policies procedures, or content of these external sites.

Data Transfer & Sharing

Where we consider it is necessary or appropriate for the purposes of data storage or processing or providing any service or product on our behalf to you, we may transfer your Personal Data to any Mercedes-Benz Group AG company, any of our related companies and subsidiaries including those established in the future, third party service or product providers, business partners and/or Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers within or outside Malaysia, under conditions of confidentiality and similar levels of security safeguards. You hereby consent to us transferring your Personal Data outside Malaysia in these instances where it may be necessary for us to transfer your Personal Data outside Malaysia if any of our service providers or business partners who are involved in providing part of our products or services are located in countries outside of Malaysia. Reasonable steps will be taken to safeguard your Personal Data whereby these service or products providers, business partners and Authorized Sales Agents and Service Dealers will not use the Personal Data for any reason other than to provide the products or services they are contracted to provide.

Data Retention

We will retain your Personal Data in compliance with this Notice for the duration of your relationship with us whether it is through the provision of any product or service, or for such period as may be necessary to protect our interests and/or where otherwise required by law including but not limited to legal commercial and legal tax record-keeping requirements. We will ensure that all Personal Data is destroyed or permanently deleted when such data is no longer required.

Social plugins

We use what are known as social plugins of social networks such as Facebook, Instagram, Twitter and Google+. When you browse or visit our website or mobile application or MBUX Multimedia System, these social plugins are deactivated as standard, i.e. without any action on your part no data is transferred to the operators of these social networks. If you wish to use one of the social networks, you can activate them by clicking on the relevant social plug-in to establish a connection to the server of the network concerned.

If you have a user account with the corresponding social network and you are logged in to this specific social network at the time you activate the social plug-in, this social network can attribute your visit to our websites or our mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System to your user account. If you would like to prevent this, please log out from the social network prior to activating the social plug-in. A social network is unable to attribute a visit to other Mercedes-Benz websites or mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System before you have activated any available social plug-in there.

If you activate a social plug-in, the network directly transfers the consequently available data to your browser, which integrates it into our websites, mobile applications and/or MBUX Multimedia System. In this situation there may also be data transfers that are initiated and controlled by the corresponding social network. Your connection with a social network, the data transfer which takes place between the network and your system, and your interactions on this platform are subject solely to the data protection provisions of the network concerned.

The social plugin remains active until you deactivate it again or delete your cookies. You can find more detailed information on cookies in our cookie notes.

When you click on a link to an offer or activate a social plug-in, it is possible that Personal Data may reach providers in countries outside of Malaysia. Please consider this before clicking on a link or activating a social plug-in and thereby initiating a transfer of your data.

For the operation, optimisation and security of our websites, mobile applications and MBUX Multimedia System we also use qualified service providers (e.g. IT service providers, marketing agencies). We only pass on Personal Data to these service providers if so required for the provision and use of the websites, mobile applications, MBUX Multimedia System and their functionalities, for the pursuit of legitimate interests, to meet legal obligations or insofar as you have consented to such processing of Personal Data in this Notice.

Evaluation of usage data & interest-related information

We use Adobe Analytics and Google Analytics products in order to be able to detect visitors’ preferences and particularly popular parts of our internet offer. This enables us to provide content that is more accurately suited to your needs, and in so doing improve our service.

We also use what are known as retargeting technologies in order to be able to show you content matching your interests and requirements on our websites, mobile applications and MBUX Multimedia System. Your interest in our products and services is stored in cookies to this end. These cookies are processed during a visit to our websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System. This takes place in an anonymised fashion, i.e. you cannot be identified through retargeting.

If you do not want us to collect, save and analyse information on your visit and if you do not want to receive information on Mercedes-Benz websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System in line with your interests you can object to this at any time for the future (opt out).

An opt-out cookie is set in your browser for technical implementation of this rejection. This cookie serves exclusively to assign your rejection. Please note that for technical reasons an opt-out cookie can only be used for the browser from which it was set. If you delete the cookies or use another browser or another end device you must opt out again.

User-based information (targeting and retargeting)

We also use what are known as retargeting technologies in order to be able to match our online marketing (e.g. banner advertising) more specifically to your requirements and interests on the websites or mobile applications of our retargeting partners (not limited to Flashtalking, Google Adwords, Google Doubleclick, Vivaki, Salesforce DMP and Adobe Target). Your interest in our products and services is stored in cookies to this end. These cookies are processed and used when visiting other websites or mobile applications which cooperate with our retargeting partners, in order to be able to provide you with information related as closely as possible to your interests. This takes place in an anonymised fashion, i.e. you cannot be identified through retargeting.

If you do not want us and our retargeting partners to collect, save and analyse information about your visit, or to match banner advertising to your interests, you can reject this at any time for the future (opt out).

An opt-out cookie is set in your browser for technical implementation of this rejection. This cookie serves exclusively to assign your rejection. Please note that for technical reasons an opt-out cookie can only be used for the browser from which it was set. If you delete the cookies or use another browser or another end device you must opt out again.

Your Right of Access and Correction

In order to provide you with effective and continuous Products and Services, it is required that you provide us with accurate and complete Personal Data, failing which we may not be able to process your request or application. You may request access to your Personal Data (at a prescribed fee), and/or correct your Personal Data which is inaccurate, incomplete, misleading or not current, if necessary. You may contact us using the contact details found in our website or in this Notice.

We provide this Notice in both English and Bahasa Malaysia. In case of any inconsistencies between these two, the English version shall prevail. In case there are any inconsistencies on how we collect or use your personal data between this Notice and the terms and conditions of your specific Products and Services or other contractual documents, the terms and conditions of your specific Products or Services or other contractual documents shall prevail.

In the event that you do not approve of our use of your Personal Data for any other purpose apart from the purpose for which your information was provided to us, you may inform us of this by contacting us using the contact details found in our website or in this Notice, and we shall take all reasonable efforts to comply with your request and in accordance with the personal data protection law and regulation of Malaysia.

Cookies

a) Cookies may be used when you are visiting our websites, mobile applications and MBUX Multimedia System. Technically, these are so-called HTML cookies and similar software tools such as Web/DOM Storage or Local Shared Objects (so-called “Flash cookies”), which we collectively refer to as cookies. We also use cookies to show you usage-based content and advertising which we work with selected partners (e.g. Google, Facebook, Salesforce and TradeDesk).

b) Cookies are small files that are stored on your desktop, laptop or mobile device while you visit a website, mobile application or MBUX Multimedia System. Cookies make it possible, for example, to determine whether there has already been a connection between the device and the websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System; take into account your preferred language or other settings, offer you certain functions (e.g. online shop, vehicle configurator) or recognise your usage-based interests. Cookies may also contain personal data which we may share with any Mercedes-Benz Group AG company (e.g. Mercedes-AMG GmbH and Mercedes-Benz Mobility AG) to improve the usage-based content and advertising shown to you.

c) Whether and which cookies are used when you visit our websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System depends on which areas and functions of our websites, mobile applications and MBUX Multimedia System you use and whether you agree to the use of cookies that are not technically required in our Consent Management System. You will find further information and decision-making options here: https://www.mercedes-benz.com.my/passengercars/content-pool/tool-pages/legal/cookies.html

d) The use of cookies also depends on the settings of the web browser you are using (e.g., Microsoft Edge, Google Chrome, Apple Safari, Mozilla Firefox). Most web browsers are preset to automatically accept certain types of cookies; however, you can usually change this setting. You can delete stored cookies at any time. Web/DOM storage and local shared objects can be deleted separately. You can find out how this works in the browser or device you are using in the manual of the learner.

e) The consent to, and rejection or deletion of, cookies are tied to the device and also to the respective web browser you use. If you use multiple devices or web browsers, you can make decisions or settings differently.

f) If you decide against the use of cookies or delete them, you may not have access to all functions of our websites, mobile applications or MBUX Multimedia System or individual functions may be limited.

Newsletter

If you subscribe to a newsletter which is offered by us, the data you provide when registering for the newsletter will be used solely for the purpose of sending out the newsletter, unless you consent to any use beyond this. You can end the subscription at any time via the unsubscribe option in the newsletter.

Central Mercedes-Benz Group AG access service

The central Mercedes-Benz Group AG company access service enables you to create a single user account to log in to MBUX Multimedia System and all websites and mobile applications of the Mercedes-Benz Group AG company and the brands that are offered through this service. The applicable terms of use contain special data protection provisions. You can access these terms of use on the respective log-in pages of the connected websites and applications.

Changes to Privacy Notice

We reserve the right to amend this Notice from time to time without prior notice. The updated version of this Notice shall be available on our website.

Contact Us

You may direct inquiries, comments or complaints by submitting them in writing to:

